  "narrative": {
    "theme_description": "The DeepVein Mining Company's deepest excavation struck an ancient sealed vault. The automated guardians left by its builders activated, slaughtering the miners. Months later, the company sent enforcers — they never returned. The mine was sealed and officially listed as 'depleted.'",
    "room_text_pool": [
      {
        "text": "Mining carts sit on rusted tracks, overturned. Pickaxes lie scattered as if dropped mid-swing.",
        "type": "combat"
      },
      {
        "text": "The ceiling groans ominously overhead. Dust sifts down with every footstep.",
        "type": "event"
      },
      {
        "text": "A safety notice board still hangs on the wall. Someone has scrawled 'THEY'RE ALIVE' over the safety guidelines.",
        "type": "event"
      },
      {
        "text": "An untouched break room — half-eaten meals on the table, mugs of long-cold coffee. No bodies.",
        "type": "rest"
      },
      {
        "text": "Veins of glittering ore run through the walls. Whatever they mined here was worth dying for.",
        "type": "treasure"
      },
      {
        "text": "The air smells of machine oil and something older — like stone that has never seen sunlight.",
        "type": "combat"
      },
      {
        "text": "A powered-down automaton slumped against the wall stirs as you approach. Its eyes flicker red.",
        "type": "combat"
      },
      {
        "text": "Deep gouges in the stone floor trace the path of something massive being dragged through here.",
        "type": "event"
      },
      {
        "text": "Water drips into a pool, the sound echoing for far too long in the darkness ahead.",
        "type": "event"
      },
      {
        "text": "A foreman's ledger lies open: 'Day 89 — They found the door. I've ordered it opened. God help us.'",
        "type": "event"
      }
    ],
